.TH "drm_gem_lock_reservations" 9 "drm_gem_lock_reservations" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_lock_reservations \- Sets up the ww context and acquires the lock on an array of GEM objects.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_gem_lock_reservations
.BI "(struct drm_gem_object **objs "  ","
.BI "int count "  ","
.BI "struct ww_acquire_ctx *acquire_ctx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "objs" 12
drm_gem_objects to lock
.IP "count" 12
Number of objects in \fIobjs\fP
.IP "acquire_ctx" 12
struct ww_acquire_ctx that will be initialized as
part of tracking this set of locked reservations.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Once you've locked your reservations, you'll want to set up space
for your shared fences (if applicable), submit your job, then
\fBdrm_gem_unlock_reservations\fP.
